Which file is used to provide a list of users that can add and delete cron jobs?
A)  /etc/cron.job
B)  /etc/cron.allow
C)  /etc/cron.users
D)  /etc/crontab
B
B. The /etc/cron.allow file is a list of users who have permission to create and remove theirown cron jobs. The /etc/crontab file is used to store cron jobs. The other files do not exist.Chapter 1: System Management (Domain 1.0)191
